treatment.description:
Plants terrestrial or semiaquatic, erect to decumbent, 10–90 cm. Leaves scattered
        along stem and gradually reduced to sheathing bracts; blade ascending, linear-lanceolate to
        lanceolate, narrowly elliptic, or oblanceolate, 3–25 × 1–4.5 cm. Inflorescences: floral
        bracts spreading to ascending, lanceolate, 15–90 × 5–12 mm. Flowers ascending, not showy;
        sepals 3–7 × 3–4 mm; dorsal sepal shallowly concave; lateral sepals reflexed-spreading;
        petals greenish, lamina ascending, falcate, 3–7 × 1 mm, lateral lobe arcuately
        spreading-ascending, filiform, slightly to markedly exceeding petal; lip greenish, middle
        lobe descending, linear, 4–7 × 1 mm, lateral lobes ascending-spreading, filiform, 5–11 mm;
        spur slenderly cylindric to scarcely club-shaped, 0.8–1.4 cm; ovaries 9–15 mm. Capsules on
        short pedicel, nearly erect, 8–15 × 3–7 mm,
